qas.question: What do the letters identify in a bulb shape designation?
What do the numbers identify in a bulb shape designation?
Can the name of a certain bulb shape vary?

answers.text: The names of the shapes may be slightly different in some regions

qas.question: What units are the bulb sizes measured in?

answers.text: 1⁄8 of an inch, or in millimeters

qas.question: What does not come in a range of shapes and sizes?
What is not different in some regions?

plausible_answers.text: consisting of one or more letters followed by one or more numbers, e.g. A55 or PAR38

qas.question: How are incandescent light bulbs not designated?
What must the letters not represent on a bulb?

plausible_answers.text: the maximum diameter, either in 1⁄8 of an inch, or in millimeters, depending on the shape and the region
